The `consumeBytes` method returns a boolean that indicates whether or not a threshold was reached meaning a window update can be sent for the stream (i.e. to say that the stream can send more data).

The method does a `ctx.write` with the window update frame, but doesn&#39;t flush it. So if nothing is flushing the context, you need to do that:

```java
if (flowController.consumeBytes(stream, processed)) {
    ctx.flush();
}
```

